{{Korean name|Lee}}

'''Lee Min-Kyu''' ({{lang-ko|<U+C774><U+BBFC><U+ADDC>}}; born 6 January 1989) is a [[South Korea]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Defender (football)|Defender]], who plays for [[Gangwon FC]] in the [[K-League]].

==Club career==
After completing his university education at [[Hongik University]], Lee was placed on the 2011 intake of the K-League draft.  Joining [[Gangwon FC]] as their fourth choice pick, his first game for his new club was as a starter in the second round match of the [[2011 K-League Cup]] against the [[Chunnam Dragons]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.soccerway.com/matches/2011/04/06/korea-republic/k-league-cup/gangwon-fc/chunnam-dragons/1083008/ |title=Gangwon FC vs. Chunnam Dragons 0 - 0 |publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> Four days later on 10 April, Lee made his debut in the [[K-League]] itself, playing in Gangwon's 1 - 0 loss to [[Ulsan Hyundai]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.soccerway.com/matches/2011/04/10/korea-republic/k-league/ulsan-horang-i/gangwon-fc/1084158/ |title=Ulsan Hyundai vs. Gangwon FC 0 - 1 |publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref>  

